The paper also discusses the use of Binary Decision Diagrams, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could be another relevant sub-category. The paper's focus on propositional logic and its operators suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper's use of interval-based reasoning and its focus on model construction suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) could be another relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on systematic reduction of infinite-time reasoning to finite-time reasoning suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) could also be a relevant sub-category.
